Great breakfast spot in the Gothic quarter.  The owners were friendly and helpful, and the food was fantastic.  My wife's eggs benedict were especially good.  My omelette was good too, but her's really showed how much better eggs are outside of the US.  So rich and a darker yellow yolk!  What do we do to ours?  I digress, Milk is a great spot for breakfast.  It still doesn't open that early.  If you have jet lag, and want breakfast at 7am, you'll have to wait!  Place doesn't open until 10, but it's totally worth it.
